definition.value: A cholesterol ester in which the acyl group contains 22 carbons in total and 4 double bonds.
A cholesterol ester in which the acyl group contains 20 carbons in total and 2 double bonds.
A cholesterol ester in which the acyl group contains 20 carbons in total and 1 double bond.
A 20-oxo steroid that is pregnenolone carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at the 7beta-position.
A 3beta-hydroxy-Delta(5)-steroid that is pregnenolone carrying an oxo group at position 7.
A 3beta-hydroxy-Delta(5)-steroid that is  dehydroepiandrosterone carrying an additional oxo group at position 7.
A 3beta-hydroxy steroid that is epiandrosterone carrying a hydroxy group at the 7beta position. It is an endogenous androgen metabolite that has been shown to exert neuroprotective effects.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 44 with 6 double bonds.
A diamino acid that is alanine in which one of the hydrogens of the methyl group is replaced by an amino group.
